(77,'ANTH',4700,'Issues in Contemporary Anthropological Theory',0.50,'This course critically examines current anthropological theories, which may include post-structuralism, post-modernism, neo-Marxism and processual approaches. Attention may also be given to the theoretical and political implications of constructionism and calls for ethnographic reflexivity.','Department of Sociology and Anthropology','Guelph','12.50 credits including ANTH*3690, SOAN*3070',91,12.50),
